# Passing Data Down

**Props** (short for properties) are read‑only inputs to a component. They are passed from a parent component to a child component, similar to function arguments.

In a functional component, props are the first parameter:

```jsx
function Greeting(props) {
  return <h1>Hello, {props.name}!</h1>;
}

// Usage
<Greeting name="Alice" />
```

Props can be any JavaScript value: strings, numbers, booleans, objects, arrays, functions, even other components.

slides.codeSnippet:
function UserCard(props) {
  return (
    <div>
      <h2>{props.name}</h2>
      <p>Age: {props.age}</p>
      <p>Active: {props.isActive ? 'Yes' : 'No'}</p>
    </div>
  );
}

// Parent
<UserCard name="Bob" age={30} isActive={true} />
